Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Place green beans in #oven-ready tray{1} (for 4 servings, divide between two
trays). Toss with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@salt{1/2%tsp}, and @black pepper{1/2%tsp}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
half the @ranch spice{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and
pepper; place on top of green beans (for 4 servings, divide chicken between
two trays).

Brush the top of each chicken cutlet with @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Sprinkle with
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, pressing to
adhere. Top with a drizzle of oil.

Roast on middle rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until green beans are
tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4 servings,
place both trays, side by side, on middle rack.)

Once chicken and green beans have roasted ~{12%minutes}, place sealed bag of
@microwavable multicolor baby potatoes{12%ounce}, front side down, in the
#microwave{}. Microwave until tender, ~{5%minutes}. Let cool in the microwave
for ~{2%minutes}.

> Potatoes can also be microwaved in a large microwave-safe bowl covered with
> plastic wrap.

Carefully remove potatoes from microwave (use a #kitchen towel{} or #oven mitt{}
the bag will be hot!) and open bag (watch out for steam). Add remaining
ranch spice, @butter{1%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, and pepper to bag with potatoes;
toss to coat.

> Alternatively, transfer potatoes to a large bowl to season.

Divide crunchy ranch chicken, green beans, and potatoes between plates in
separate sections. Serve.